An intelligence driven operation along the M4, by detectives from the Provincial Organised Crime Investigation Unit, yielded the arrest of a 20-year-old man who was caught in possession of 54 medicine containers labelled as Mylan Alprazolam (Xanax), on Wednesday. Provincial spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele, said that on 22 July at 1.30pm, detectives from the Provincial Organised Crime Investigation Unit, conducted an intelligence driven operation along the M4 freeway north bound. “Following a rigorous investigation, they stopped a vehicle and conducted a search. During a search of the vehicle, police discovered 54 medicine containers labelled as Mylan Alprazolam (Xanax) covered with a big jacket. The suspect failed to produce necessary documents for the drugs when he was questioned. He was immediately arrested and detained at the Umbilo police station,” Mbele said. The suspect appeared in the Durban Magistrate’s Court for contravention
of the Medicines Control Act 101 of 1965. The provincial commissioner in KwaZulu-Natal, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula commended detectives from the Provincial Organised Crime Investigation Unit for the arrest.